snippet.textDisplay:
I realize this is all fun and games and that St. Louis is the home team, but how this skills challenge was handled was extremely disappointing and ridiculous.

The best man should win. No impromptu bonus shots for the home home team, and no adding points (at least one of those shots O’Reilly took didn’t hit anything, but he got points).

Congrats to Patrick Kane. He won fair and square, even in the face of IMMENSE cheating.
snippet.textOriginal:
I realize this is all fun and games and that St. Louis is the home team, but how this skills challenge was handled was extremely disappointing and ridiculous.  

The best man should win.  No impromptu bonus shots for the home home team, and no adding points (at least one of those shots O’Reilly took didn’t hit anything, but he got points).  

Congrats to Patrick Kane.  He won fair and square, even in the face of IMMENSE cheating.

snippet.textDisplay: The way this competition was set up and scored made it horribly disappointing, confusing, and not fun to watch. Bouncing off the ice into a target scores points but hitting the 10 point board directly in flight doesnt? The small 2 and 4 point targets were pretty much pointless and Marner clearly scored 10 three times and only got credit for twice. This trash game needs a complete overhaul in design and scoring rules or else it should just be scrapped all together. Sorry NHL but this was a complete fail and then some. Time to go back to the drawing board with this one.
